      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:49:18",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ حُسْنَ الْخُلُقِ يَبْلُغُ بِصَاحِبِهِ دَرَجَةَ الصَّائِمِ الْقَائِمِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The good manners makes its owner to reach the level of the Fasting one, the standing one (in <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span>)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "18. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sinan from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) has said, ‘Excellence in moral behavior takes one to the level of those who worship all nights and fast all days.’” "
        ]
      }
